-content:deploy --theme Magento/backend --theme Vendor/yourtheme</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used to exclude the specfic theme when you are deploying the static content.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --exclude-theme Magento/luma</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used to generate files only for the specified areas.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --area adminhtml</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not generate files for the specified areas.\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --exclude-area adminhtml</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy JavaScript files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-javascript</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy Images files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-image</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy CSS files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-css</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy LESS files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-less</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy HTML files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-html</pre><br/>\r\n \r\n<strong>Magento Cache Clean Command</strong><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will delete all items from enabled Magento cache types only and it will not affect other processes or applications because it cleans only the cache that Magento uses.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:clean</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will be flushing a cache type purges the cache storage, which might affect other processes applications that are using the same storage.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:flush</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will show the status of all avaialble caches.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:status\r\n\r\n       Current status:\r\n                        config: 1\r\n                        layout: 1\r\n         