ndex indexer_name</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will show the mode of all indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento indexer:show-mode</pre>\r\n\r\n<strong>Other Useful Commands</strong><br/><br/>\r\nThe command will show the status list of all modules.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento module:status</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will check the current mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento deploy:mode:show</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will change the mode to developer mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magentodeploy:mode:setdeveloper</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will change the mode to production mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magentodeploy:mode:set production</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nI hope this documentation will help you and we will continue to share more blogs in future.\r\n\r\nEnjoy Coding:)','Magento 2 Commands','','inherit','closed','closed','','471-revision-v1','','','2017-10-23 10:04:18','2017-10-23 10:04:18','',471,'http://axovel.com/471-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(492,1,'2017-10-23 10:06:14','2017-10-23 10:06:14','As many developers are searching the different website for SSH/CLI commands for Magento 2.In this tutorial, we will cover all the helpful commands which are frequently used in the Magento2 development and help the Magento developers to get all the possible list of commands and enjoy the development.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<strong>Magento Setup Upgrade Command</strong><br/><br/>\r\nThe command is used if you have installed a new module or enable one or more modules then use this command.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:upgrade</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n--keep-generated is optional parameter it will not remove pub/static files while installing and updating the database. <br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:upgrade --keep-generated</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Magento Static Content Deploy Command</strong><br/>\r\nThe command is used to regenerate your static content.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command is used for static content d