ento setup:static-content:deploy --theme Magento/backend --theme Vendor/yourtheme</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used to exclude the specfic theme when you are deploying the static content.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --exclude-theme Magento/luma</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used to generate files only for the specified areas.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --area adminhtml</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not generate files for the specified areas.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --exclude-area adminhtml</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy JavaScript files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-javascript</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy Images files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-image</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy CSS files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-css</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy LESS files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-less</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command is used for not deploy HTML files.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy --no-html</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Magento Cache Clean Command</strong><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will delete all items from enabled Magento cache types only and it will not affect other processes or applications because it cleans only the cache that Magento uses.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:clean</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will be flushing a cache type purges the cache storage, which might affect other processes applications that are using the same storage.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:flush</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will show the status of all available caches.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:status\r\n\r\n       Current status:\r\n                        config: 1\r\n                        layout: 1\r\n                    block_html: 1\r\n                   collections: 1\r\n                    reflection: 1\r\n                        db_ddl: 1\r\n                           eav: 1\r\n            config_integration: 1\r\n        config_integration_api: 1\r\n                     full_page: 1\r\n                     translate: 1\r\n             config_webservice: 1</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will enable the all cache type.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:enable</pre><br/>\r\nThe command will enable the specific cache type.<br/>\r\n<pre>  php bin/magento cache:enable [cache_type]\r\n\r\n  For e.g php bin/magento cache:enable config\r\n</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will disable all the cache type.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:disable</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will disable the specific cache type.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento cache:disable [cache_type]\r\n\r\nFor e.g php bin/magento cache:disable layout\r\n</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n<strong>Enable, Disable and Unistall Magento Module</strong><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will enable the module in magento 2.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magentomodule:enable Namespace_Module</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will disable the module in magento 2.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento module:disable Namespace_Module</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will uninstall the module in magento 2.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento module:uninstall Namespace_Module</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Magento indexing commands</strong><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will show the list of indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento indexer:info</pre><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will show the status of indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento indexer:status</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will reindex all the indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento indexer:reindex</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will reindex specific indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin\\magento indexer:reindex indexer_name</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will show the mode of all indexers.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento indexer:show-mode</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n<strong>Other Useful Commands</strong><br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe command will show the status list of all modules.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento module:status</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will check the current mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magento deploy:mode:show</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will change the mode to developer mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magentodeploy:mode:setdeveloper</pre><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nThe command will change the mode to production mode.<br/>\r\n<pre>php bin/magentodeploy:mode:set production</pre><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nI hope this documentation will help you and we will continue to share more blogs in future.\r\n\r\nEnjoy Coding:)','Magento 2 Commands','','inherit','closed','closed','','471-revision-v1','','','2017-10-23 10:38:40','2017-10-23 10:38:40','',471,'http://axovel.com/471-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(498,1,'2017-11-02 07:31:11','2017-11-02 07:31:11','<h2>Magento 2 Event List</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table style=\"height: 10583px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"598\" cellspacing=\"0\"><colgroup width=\"200\"></colgroup> <colgroup width=\"200\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><b><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">File</span></b></td>\r\n<td align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">Event name</span></b></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">Authorizenet/Controller/Directpost/Payment/Place.php</span></td>\r\n<td align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">checkout_directpost_placeOrder</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" height=\"17\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">Backend/Block/System/Store/Edit/AbstractForm.php</span></td>\r\n<td align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Liberation Serif\';\">adminhtml_store_edit_form_pre